headline: Marsh McLennan (MMC): Net Margin Dip Challenges Profit Growth Narrative Despite Valuation Discount
summary: Marsh & McLennan Companies (MMC) reported earnings that are forecast to grow 8.4% per year, while revenue is expected to increase at 4.9% annually. Net profit margins came in at 16%, just below last year’s 17%, and recent annual earnings grew by 2.9% compared to a five-year average of 13.4% per year.
